; VICE monitor startup script — used by 'make vice-debug' for interactive debugging.
; Loaded via -moncommands tests/setup.mon with -initbreak reset, so it runs
; before the CPU starts and before the test program loads.
;
; Oscar64 -g writes into the .lbl file:
;   al xxxx .symbol_name  — address labels for all C functions
;   break xxxx            — auto-breakpoints at breakpoint() call sites
;
; Loading the .lbl file activates:
;   'break 5577' — fires for all overlay6 operations (import/export SEQ).
;   Oscar64 inlines the tiny overlay6 wrapper functions into mainmenuloop,
;   so all four cases (42-45) converge to the NOP at $5577 before JMP $553e.
;   Overlay3/5 breakpoints compile to NOPs in overlay code with no .lbl break
;   entry; use 'break $553e' (mainmenuloop top) manually for those operations.
;
ll build/vdcse_test.lbl
; Resume CPU execution (needed when launched with -monitorbreak reset)
g
